title: Mumbai meat ban: Raj Thackeray’s MNS workers to sell mutton at Dadar in protest
text:
Other Articles RIL bets big on start-ups to help lob India into global league Jamie Foxx in talks for 'Baby Driver' Uber cabs signs pact with Tamil Nadu govt to create over 30,000 jobs In a protest against the four day meat ban in the state, the Raj Thackeray-led Maharashtra Navnirman Sena (MNS) party workers will sell mutton at Agar Bazar in Mumbai’s Dadar today.
The banning of meat in Mumbai have turned into a political slugfest with various political parties slamming the Maharashtra Government for imposing such ban.
The Maharashtra government has banned meat in Mumbai for four days, in view of the Jain festival of Paryushan.
 10, 2015 11:02 am
